WEBVTT



00:00:00.544 --> 00:00:09.952
Hello friends, I'm Rick Warren and welcome to Spurgeon's Sermons. This is the official podcast brought to you by Premier and Spurgeon's College.

00:00:09.920 --> 00:00:19.968
You know the teachings of Charles Spurgeon have had a personal impact on my life in a profound way and I'm confident they'll do the same for you. So get ready to be challenged.

00:00:19.488 --> 00:00:28.224
be challenged, equipped, and guided by Charles Spurgeon, who is universally regarded as the greatest English preacher in the history of the Church.

00:00:29.632 --> 00:00:32.000
Supposing him to be the gardener.

00:00:32.768 --> 00:00:35.072
A sermon by Charles Spurgeon.

00:00:35.168 --> 00:00:36.416
Part two.

00:00:37.472 --> 00:00:40.064
Supposing him to be the gardener.

00:00:40.672 --> 00:00:43.104
John's Gospel chapter 20

00:00:43.104 --> 00:00:44.608
Verse 15

00:00:46.080 --> 00:00:47.456
Dear friends,

00:00:47.456 --> 00:00:50.720
There is one mercy with regard to this church.

00:00:50.624 --> 00:00:53.216
which I have often had to thank God for.

00:00:53.440 --> 00:00:54.656
Namely,

00:00:54.400 --> 00:00:58.560
That evils should have been shut out for so long a time.

00:00:59.616 --> 00:01:04.032
During the period in which we've been together as pastor and people,

00:01:04.192 --> 00:01:06.880
And that is now some twenty-nine years.

00:01:06.912 --> 00:01:10.240
We have enjoyed uninterrupted prosperity.

00:01:10.240 --> 00:01:12.928
Going from strength to strength

00:01:12.672 --> 00:01:14.432
In the work of the Lord.

00:01:14.880 --> 00:01:16.032
Alas!

00:01:16.032 --> 00:01:20.640
We have seen many other churches that were quite as hopeful as our own.

00:01:20.480 --> 00:01:22.432
Rent with strife,

00:01:22.400 --> 00:01:24.832
Brought low by disunity,

00:01:25.024 --> 00:01:27.360
Or overthrown by heresy.

00:01:28.160 --> 00:01:29.152
I hope

00:01:28.992 --> 00:01:33.120
We have not been apt to judge their faults severely.

00:01:33.856 --> 00:01:39.744
But we must be thankful for our own deliverance from the evils which have afflicted them.

00:01:40.576 --> 00:01:42.752
I do not know how it is.

00:01:42.592 --> 00:01:45.536
That we have been kept together in love.

00:01:45.312 --> 00:01:47.904
Helped to abound in labour,

00:01:47.808 --> 00:01:50.720
And enabled to be firm in the face.

00:01:50.624 --> 00:01:53.632
Unless it be that special grace

00:01:53.408 --> 00:01:55.296
Has watched over us.

00:01:55.840 --> 00:01:57.696
We are full of faults.

00:01:57.952 --> 00:02:00.384
We have nothing to boast of.

00:02:00.672 --> 00:02:04.992
And yet no church has been more divinely favoured.

00:02:05.472 --> 00:02:06.752
I wonder...

00:02:06.592 --> 00:02:09.504
That the blessing should have lasted so long.

00:02:09.568 --> 00:02:11.584
And I cannot make it out.

00:02:11.776 --> 00:02:15.104
Except when I fall into supposing him.

00:02:15.232 --> 00:02:16.768
To be the gardener.

00:02:17.952 --> 00:02:22.560
I cannot trace our prosperity to the pastor, certainly.

00:02:22.816 --> 00:02:26.816
Nor even to my beloved friends, the elders and deacons.

00:02:26.688 --> 00:02:31.424
Nor even to the best of you with your fervent love and holy zeal.

00:02:31.872 --> 00:02:35.104
I think it must be that Jesus

00:02:35.104 --> 00:02:36.800
Has been the gardener.

00:02:37.312 --> 00:02:39.392
And he has shut the gate.

00:02:39.360 --> 00:02:41.920
When I am afraid, I have left it open.

00:02:42.272 --> 00:02:50.016
And he has driven out the wild boar of the wood just when he had entered to root up the weaker plants.

00:02:50.688 --> 00:02:53.440
He must have been about at nights.

00:02:53.376 --> 00:02:56.256
To keep off the prowling thieves.

00:02:56.640 --> 00:03:00.288
And he must have been here too in the noontide heat.

00:03:00.160 --> 00:03:04.352
To guard those of you who have prospered in worldly goods.

00:03:04.192 --> 00:03:06.976
From the glare of too bright a sun.

00:03:07.904 --> 00:03:08.992
Yes.

00:03:08.864 --> 00:03:11.168
He has been with us.

00:03:11.136 --> 00:03:12.992
Blessed be his name.

00:03:13.344 --> 00:03:14.560
From him.

00:03:14.368 --> 00:03:19.040
Has come all this peace and unity and enthusiasm.

00:03:19.808 --> 00:03:23.520
May we never grieve him so that he shall turn away from us.

00:03:23.648 --> 00:03:28.224
But rather let us invite him, saying, Abide with us.

00:03:28.544 --> 00:03:35.008
Thou that dwellest in the gardens, let this be one of the gardens in which thou dost deign to dwell.

00:03:34.848 --> 00:03:36.768
Until the daybreak.

00:03:36.544 --> 00:03:38.720
And the shadows flee away.

00:03:40.512 --> 00:03:47.360
Let your imaginations run along with mine while I say that supposing him to be the gardener,

00:03:47.040 --> 00:03:50.496
Should be a spur to many duties.

00:03:50.944 --> 00:03:53.248
One of the duties of a Christian

00:03:53.184 --> 00:03:54.432
Is joy.

00:03:55.200 --> 00:03:57.472
That is a blessed religion.

00:03:57.280 --> 00:04:01.632
Which among its precepts commands men and women to be happy.

00:04:02.336 --> 00:04:04.704
When joy becomes a duty,

00:04:04.768 --> 00:04:06.976
Who would wish to neglect it?

00:04:07.648 --> 00:04:10.944
Surely it must help every little plant.

00:04:10.624 --> 00:04:13.024
To drink in the sunlight.

00:04:13.600 --> 00:04:17.504
When it is whispered among the flowers that Jesus is the gardener,

00:04:17.952 --> 00:04:19.488
Oh, you say,

00:04:19.200 --> 00:04:21.728
I am such a little plant.

00:04:21.408 --> 00:04:23.488
8. I do not grow well. 9.

00:04:23.584 --> 00:04:26.784
I do not put forth so much foliage.

00:04:26.752 --> 00:04:31.584
Nor are there so many flowers on me as are many round about me.

00:04:32.544 --> 00:04:34.208
It is quite right.

00:04:34.368 --> 00:04:37.024
That you should think little of yourself.

00:04:37.408 --> 00:04:38.560
Perhaps

00:04:38.400 --> 00:04:41.760
To droop your head is a part of your beauty.

00:04:42.048 --> 00:04:45.504
Many flowers had not been half so lovely.

00:04:45.376 --> 00:04:49.472
If they had not practised the art of hanging their heads.

00:04:50.080 --> 00:04:52.832
But supposing him to be the gardener,

00:04:52.864 --> 00:04:56.128
Then he is as much a gardener to you,

00:04:55.808 --> 00:04:59.872
As he is to the most grand palm in the whole domain.

00:05:00.640 --> 00:05:05.664
In the Mentone garden right before me grew the orange and the aloe,

00:05:05.696 --> 00:05:09.248
And others of the finer and more noticeable plants.

00:05:09.632 --> 00:05:11.840
But on a wall to my left,

00:05:11.904 --> 00:05:14.016
Grew common wallflowers.

00:05:14.080 --> 00:05:15.616
And succulents.

00:05:15.680 --> 00:05:17.568
And tiny herbs

00:05:17.472 --> 00:05:20.896
Such as we find on our own rocky places.

00:05:21.952 --> 00:05:25.024
Now the gardener had cared for all of these.

00:05:24.832 --> 00:05:26.880
Little as well as great.

00:05:27.232 --> 00:05:34.656
In fact, there were hundreds of specimens of the most insignificant growths, all duly labelled and described.

00:05:34.624 --> 00:05:37.216
The smallest succulent could say,

00:05:37.024 --> 00:05:39.136
He is my gardener.

00:05:38.880 --> 00:05:43.680
Just as surely as he is the gardener of the Goire de Dijon.

00:05:43.936 --> 00:05:45.824
Or Mareschal Neale,

00:05:46.624 --> 00:05:51.072
O feeble child of God, the Lord takes care of you.

00:05:51.712 --> 00:05:54.816
Your heavenly father feeds ravens,

00:05:54.720 --> 00:05:57.344
And guides the flight of sparrows.

00:05:58.272 --> 00:06:02.464
Should he not much more care for you, o ye of little faith?

00:06:03.264 --> 00:06:05.344
Oh little plants!

00:06:05.632 --> 00:06:08.224
You will grow rightly enough.

00:06:08.640 --> 00:06:13.056
Perhaps you are growing downward just now rather than upward.

00:06:13.440 --> 00:06:20.480
Remember that there are plants of which we value the underground route much more than we do the stalk above the ground.

00:06:21.152 --> 00:06:24.832
Perhaps it is not yours to grow very fast.

00:06:25.312 --> 00:06:28.896
You may be a slow-growing shrub by nature.

00:06:29.568 --> 00:06:33.568
And you would not be healthy if you were to run to wood.

00:06:34.272 --> 00:06:35.328
Anyhow,

00:06:35.200 --> 00:06:39.104
Be this your joy, you are in the garden of the Lord.

00:06:38.848 --> 00:06:41.472
And supposing him to be the gardener.

00:06:41.216 --> 00:06:43.392
He will make the best of you.

00:06:43.840 --> 00:06:46.688
You cannot be in better hands.

00:06:48.896 --> 00:06:50.464
Another duty?

00:06:50.496 --> 00:06:54.592
Is that of valuing the Lord's presence and praying for it?

00:06:55.520 --> 00:06:58.528
We ought, whenever the sabbath morning dawns,

00:06:58.464 --> 00:07:04.480
To pray our well-beloved to come into his garden and eat his pleasant fruits.

00:07:04.928 --> 00:07:06.944
What can we do without him?

00:07:07.424 --> 00:07:10.976
All day long our cry should go up to him.

00:07:10.784 --> 00:07:12.096
Our Lord

00:07:12.096 --> 00:07:14.752
Behold and visit this vine.

00:07:15.008 --> 00:07:18.528
And the vineyard which thy right hand has planted.

00:07:19.008 --> 00:07:21.280
We ought to implore him.

00:07:21.216 --> 00:07:24.640
That he would come and manifest himself to us

00:07:24.608 --> 00:07:27.104
As he does not unto the world.

00:07:27.328 --> 00:07:31.264
For what is a garden if the gardener never comes near it?

00:07:31.296 --> 00:07:35.328
What is the difference between it and the wilderness?

00:07:35.328 --> 00:07:41.408
If he to whom it belongs, never lift up spade or pruny hook upon it.

00:07:42.144 --> 00:07:44.576
So that it is our necessity.

00:07:44.704 --> 00:07:49.600
that we have Christ with us, supposing him to be the gardener.

00:07:49.984 --> 00:07:51.872
And it is our bliss

00:07:51.936 --> 00:07:56.608
that we have Christ walking between our beds and borders.

00:07:56.288 --> 00:07:58.592
Watching every plant

00:07:58.560 --> 00:08:01.952
Training, tending, maturing all.

00:08:02.528 --> 00:08:06.368
Supposing him to be the gardener, it is well.

00:08:06.432 --> 00:08:09.312
For from him is our fruit found.

00:08:10.272 --> 00:08:12.672
Divided from him we are nothing.

00:08:13.280 --> 00:08:16.064
Only as he watches over us,

00:08:15.904 --> 00:08:17.984
Can we bring forth fruit?

00:08:18.624 --> 00:08:21.856
Let us have done with confidence in man.

00:08:21.760 --> 00:08:24.416
Let us forgo all attempts

00:08:24.224 --> 00:08:27.680
To supply facts of his spiritual presence

00:08:27.488 --> 00:08:28.832
By routine.

00:08:28.704 --> 00:08:29.952
Or rant,

00:08:29.792 --> 00:08:32.288
Ritualism or rowdyism.

00:08:32.736 --> 00:08:36.800
But let us pray our Lord to be ever present with us.

00:08:36.864 --> 00:08:38.752
And by that presence,

00:08:38.912 --> 00:08:41.216
To make our garden grow.

00:08:42.368 --> 00:08:44.864
Supposing him to be the gardener,

00:08:45.088 --> 00:08:47.136
There is another duty.

00:08:47.808 --> 00:08:53.472
And that is, let each one of us yield himself up entirely to him.

00:08:54.240 --> 00:08:57.920
A plant does not know how it ought to be treated.

00:08:58.208 --> 00:08:59.648
It knows not.

00:08:59.584 --> 00:09:01.472
When it should be watered.

00:09:01.728 --> 00:09:03.968
Or when it should be kept dry.

00:09:04.544 --> 00:09:10.080
A fruit tree is no judge of when it needs to be pruned or dug.

00:09:09.888 --> 00:09:11.584
Or fertilized

00:09:12.288 --> 00:09:17.632
The wit and wisdom of the garden lies not in the flowers and shrubs.

00:09:17.408 --> 00:09:19.008
But in the gardener,

00:09:20.288 --> 00:09:21.536
Now then.

00:09:21.728 --> 00:09:27.136
If you and I are here today with any self-will or carnal judgment about us,

00:09:27.264 --> 00:09:28.608
Let us seek.

00:09:28.384 --> 00:09:30.432
To lay it all aside.

00:09:30.368 --> 00:09:33.952
That we may be absolutely at our Lord's disposal.

00:09:34.912 --> 00:09:37.024
You might not be willing.

00:09:36.864 --> 00:09:41.216
To put yourself implicitly into the hand of any mere man.

00:09:41.152 --> 00:09:42.880
Pity that you should.

00:09:43.520 --> 00:09:50.784
But surely thou plant of the Lord's right hand, planting thou mayest put thyself without a question.

00:09:50.816 --> 00:09:52.832
Into his dear hand.

00:09:52.864 --> 00:09:55.456
Supposing him to be the gardener.

00:09:55.616 --> 00:09:57.536
You mayest well say,

00:09:57.536 --> 00:10:02.592
I would neither have will nor wish nor wit nor whim nor way.

00:10:02.720 --> 00:10:09.888
But I would be as nothing in the gardener's hands that he may be to me my wisdom and my all.

00:10:10.688 --> 00:10:12.704
Here, kind gardener,

00:10:12.960 --> 00:10:16.928
Your poor plant bows itself to your hand.

00:10:16.832 --> 00:10:18.784
Train me as you will.

00:10:19.584 --> 00:10:21.088
Depend upon it.

00:10:21.280 --> 00:10:27.296
Happiness lives next door to the spirit of complete acquiescence in the will of God.

00:10:28.000 --> 00:10:36.064
And it will be easy to exercise that perfect acquiescence when we suppose the lord Jesus to be the gardener.

00:10:36.704 --> 00:10:38.720
If the Lord has done it,

00:10:39.232 --> 00:10:41.312
What has a saint to say?

00:10:42.048 --> 00:10:44.128
Oh, you afflicted one!

00:10:44.128 --> 00:10:45.856
The Lord has done it

00:10:46.080 --> 00:10:47.968
Would you have it otherwise?

00:10:48.448 --> 00:10:49.408
Nay,

00:10:49.888 --> 00:10:51.648
Are you not thankful?

00:10:51.392 --> 00:10:53.248
That it is even so.

00:10:53.280 --> 00:10:57.824
Because so is the will of him in whose hand your life is.

00:10:58.240 --> 00:10:59.616
And whose?

00:10:59.520 --> 00:11:01.696
Are all your ways.

00:11:02.432 --> 00:11:05.216
The duty of submission is very plain.

00:11:05.120 --> 00:11:06.912
Supposing him

00:11:06.976 --> 00:11:08.480
To be the gardener.

00:11:09.824 --> 00:11:12.128
One more duty I would mention.

00:11:11.968 --> 00:11:14.656
Though others suggest themselves.

00:11:15.392 --> 00:11:17.952
Supposing him to be the gardener,

00:11:18.176 --> 00:11:21.696
Then let us bring forth fruit to him.

00:11:22.880 --> 00:11:28.896
I do not address a people this morning who feel no concern as to whether they serve God or not.

00:11:29.696 --> 00:11:32.672
I believe that most of you do desire

00:11:32.736 --> 00:11:34.496
To glorify God.

00:11:35.008 --> 00:11:37.504
For being saved by grace

00:11:37.632 --> 00:11:42.208
You feel a holy ambition to show forth his praises.

00:11:42.112 --> 00:11:44.800
Who has called you out of darkness,

00:11:44.800 --> 00:11:46.880
Into his marvellous light.

00:11:48.032 --> 00:11:49.280
You wish.

00:11:49.056 --> 00:11:51.680
To bring others to Christ.

00:11:51.712 --> 00:11:57.120
Because you yourselves have been brought to life and liberty in him.

00:11:58.016 --> 00:12:02.304
Now let this be a stimulus to your fruit bearing.

00:12:02.368 --> 00:12:04.480
that Jesus is the gardener.

00:12:05.536 --> 00:12:08.800
Where you have brought forth a single cluster

00:12:09.216 --> 00:12:11.136
Bring forth a hundred.

00:12:11.232 --> 00:12:14.080
Supposing him to be the gardener.

00:12:14.944 --> 00:12:17.920
If he is to have the honour of it,

00:12:17.824 --> 00:12:20.000
Then labour to do work.

00:12:19.744 --> 00:12:22.144
Which will give him great renown.

00:12:23.552 --> 00:12:29.056
If our spiritual state were to be attributed to ourselves or to our minister,

00:12:29.216 --> 00:12:31.744
Or to some of our fellow Christians,

00:12:31.744 --> 00:12:36.704
We might not feel that we were under any great necessity to be fruitful.

00:12:37.824 --> 00:12:40.064
But if Jesus be the gardener,

00:12:40.320 --> 00:12:44.768
And is to bear the blame or the honour of what we produce.

00:12:45.056 --> 00:12:48.256
Then let us use every drop of sap

00:12:48.160 --> 00:12:50.816
And strain every fibre.

00:12:50.944 --> 00:12:54.080
That to the utmost of which we are capable.

00:12:54.368 --> 00:12:57.984
We may produce a fair reward for our Lord's work.

00:12:59.296 --> 00:13:01.344
Under such tutorship,

00:13:01.152 --> 00:13:02.368
And care.

00:13:02.304 --> 00:13:05.024
We ought to become eminent scholars.

00:13:05.696 --> 00:13:08.064
Does Christ train us?

00:13:08.576 --> 00:13:12.832
Or let us never cause the world to think meanly of our master.

00:13:13.632 --> 00:13:18.496
Students feel that their alma mater deserves great things of them.

00:13:18.624 --> 00:13:22.144
So they labor to make their university renowned.

00:13:22.592 --> 00:13:27.232
And so, since Jesus is tutor and university to us,

00:13:27.360 --> 00:13:30.752
Let us feel that we are bound to reflect credit.

00:13:30.688 --> 00:13:32.832
Upon so great a teacher,

00:13:32.864 --> 00:13:35.296
Upon so divine a name.

00:13:36.448 --> 00:13:42.624
I do not know how to put it, but surely we ought to do something worthy of such a lord.

00:13:43.776 --> 00:13:51.872
Each little flower in the garden of the Lord should wear its brightest hues and put forth its rarest perfume.

00:13:52.032 --> 00:13:54.496
Because Jesus cares for it.

00:13:55.456 --> 00:13:58.176
The best of all possible good.

00:13:58.016 --> 00:13:59.776
Should be yielded.

00:13:59.584 --> 00:14:02.560
By every plant in our Father's garden.

00:14:02.688 --> 00:14:04.672
Supposing Jesus

00:14:04.544 --> 00:14:06.336
To be the gardener.

00:14:07.680 --> 00:14:09.568
Thus much then.

00:14:09.600 --> 00:14:11.488
On those two points

00:14:11.840 --> 00:14:14.080
A king to many wonders.

00:14:14.176 --> 00:14:15.520
And the spur

00:14:15.840 --> 00:14:17.504
To many duties.

00:14:18.688 --> 00:14:25.664
Thank you for listening, friends. This podcast was brought to you by Premier, in association with Spurgeon's College.

00:14:25.632 --> 00:14:29.248
